{% doc %}

  Product — Match With
  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  Small row of curated product thumbnails shown inside the PDP info column
  under the info accordion rows. Distinct from the algorithmic "You may
  also like" section at the bottom of the page:

    - Match With = **merchant-picked** per product via metafield
      (`product.metafields.custom.match_with`, list of product references).
    - You may also like = **Shopify native recommendations** (algorithmic,
      see `sections/product-recommendations.liquid`).

  Each item is rendered as a horizontal card mirroring the sibling
  Model Info card (48×48 image on the left + title / color dots / price
  stacked right, `bg-bg-surface` rounded-6 padded container). Cards stack
  vertically — one per row — so multiple pairings read cleanly at the
  narrow PDP info-column width without overflowing.

  Earlier iteration used 80×80 vertical thumbnails in a single horizontal
  row, but (a) it desynced visually with the Model Info card on the right
  and (b) horizontal-scrolled once more than 2 items were pinned at the
  narrow info-column width. The horizontal-card pattern scales down
  gracefully: 1 item = compact, 5 items = tidy stack.

  Renders nothing if the metafield is empty or missing.

  Metafield to set up in Shopify admin → Settings → Custom data → Products:
    - Namespace: custom
    - Key: match_with
    - Type: List of product references
    - Per-product: pick the products you want to pair with.

  @param {object} product - Required.

  @example
    {% render 'product-match-with', product: product %}

{% enddoc %}

{%- liquid
  assign match_with = product.metafields.custom.match_with.value
-%}

{% if match_with.size > 0 %}
  <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
    <h3 class="text-label-tight text-fg">
      {{ 'products.match_with' | t }}
    </h3>
    <ul class="flex flex-col gap-2" role="list">
      {% for related in match_with %}
        {%- comment -%}
          Resolve the related product's Color option (if any) by
          iterating rather than using `options_by_name["Color"]` — the
          `options_by_name` lookup is case-sensitive and brittle across
          merchants who might type "color"/"Colour"/etc. Mirror the
          pattern already used in `product-card.liquid`.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- liquid
          assign color_option = nil
          for option in related.options_with_values
            if option.name == 'Color'
              assign color_option = option
              break
            endif
          endfor
        -%}

        {%- comment -%}
          Card body (title + color dots + price) is captured and handed
          to the shared `product-meta-card` primitive. Card chrome
          (image, bg-surface, rounded, padding) lives in that primitive;
          Match With only owns the content that makes it a Match With
          card (vs a Model Info card, which passes a different body).
        {%- endcomment -%}
        {%- capture meta_card_body -%}
          <p class="text-[12px] font-medium uppercase truncate w-full">
            {{ related.title }}
          </p>
          {% if color_option and color_option.values.size > 0 %}
            {%- comment -%}
              Cap at 3 swatches + `+N` overflow chip (matches
              product-card convention). Each dot is 10×10 with a
              muted border so pale swatches (white, cream) stay
              visible against the `bg-bg-surface` card.
            {%- endcomment -%}
            {%- assign color_count = color_option.values.size -%}
            {%- assign max_visible = 3 -%}
            {%- assign overflow = color_count | minus: max_visible -%}
            <ul
              class="flex items-center gap-1"
              role="list"
              aria-label="{{ 'products.product.available_colors' | t }}"
            >
              {% for value in color_option.values limit: max_visible %}
                <li
                  class="block w-2.5 h-2.5 rounded-full border border-muted/30"
                  style="background-color: {% if value.swatch.color != blank %}{{ value.swatch.color }}{% else %}{{ value | downcase | escape }}{% endif %};"
                  title="{{ value }}"
                ><span class="sr-only">{{ value }}</span></li>
              {% endfor %}
              {% if overflow > 0 %}
                <li
                  class="text-[12px] text-muted ml-1"
                  aria-label="{{ 'products.product.more_colors' | t: count: overflow }}"
                >+{{ overflow }}</li>
              {% endif %}
            </ul>
          {% endif %}
          <p class="text-[12px]">
            {{ related.price | money_without_trailing_zeros }}
          </p>
        {%- endcapture -%}

        <li>
          {% render 'product-meta-card',
                    href: related.url,
                    image: related.featured_image,
                    alt: related.title,
                    body: meta_card_body
          %}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </div>
{% endif %}
